The paper discusses the design of a platform architecture for multi-tenant blockchain-based systems, which involves addressing challenges related to data and performance isolation, scalability, and data privacy. This aligns with several sub-categories in computer science, including Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Databases (cs.DB), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). However, given the focus on distributed systems and security, cs.DC and cs.CR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.SE, cs.DB, and cs.DS.
